last_episode_to_air.name: The Winner Is...
last_episode_to_air.overview: The grand finale has arrived as the top three queens must perform their personal queer anthem as well as a showstopper number. Who will come out on top to be crowned "Queen of the Universe" and win the life-changing cash prize of $250,000?

name: Queen of the Universe
overview: Eurovision-like singing competition featuring drag queens from around the world who compete to be crowned the Ultimate Queen of the Universe
tagline: 10 international queens. 1 out of this world singing competition.

episodes.name: This Is Me (Part 1)
episodes.overview: Expect high heels, high octaves and high drama that'll blow your wig off as we meet the queens who will be competing for the $250,000 prize and the title of QUEEN OF THE UNIVERSE.

episodes.name: This Is Me (Part 2)
episodes.overview: The global drag singing competition continues as new queens arrive - and some must face elimination. Who will move forward to win the $250,000 prize and the title of QUEEN OF THE UNIVERSE?

episodes.name: Turn Back Time
episodes.overview: The queens "turn back time" with looks and performances from an important era in their lives. For the first time, the studio audience will vote for their favorites--who will survive?

episodes.name: Duets
episodes.overview: There's a shocking twist in store for the remaining queens as they are forced to pair up and perform original duets in hopes to win over the studio audience and the "Pop Diva Panel".

episodes.name: Bad Girls
episodes.overview: It's the semifinals of the global search and time for the queens to unleash their wild sides as they sing songs from their favorite iconic "bad girl" artists in hopes of securing a spot in the finale.

episodes.name: Bigger Hits, Glossier Lips, and Massive T**s
episodes.overview: Ten new queens from around the globe hit the stage and must perform their personal drag anthem while showcasing a look dedicated to their homeland. With new judge Mel B joining the Pop Diva Panel, the queens quickly learn to expect the unexpected!

episodes.name: A Spicy Twist
episodes.overview: As the queens react to Mel's "Scary News" the contestants continue to perform their personal drag anthem while rocking a look inspired by their country. But when the judges announce a "Spicy Twist" who will rise to the top and who will be eliminated?

episodes.name: Double Trouble
episodes.overview: It's duet's week! The queens find themselves in pairs as they must write lyrics to original songs and perform as a duo. Can these queens work together well enough to stay in the competition? Or will their egos and personal ambition get in the way?

episodes.name: Dragging Up the Past
episodes.overview: The seven remaining queens serve songs and looks inspired by their very first time in drag. Emotions run high as the queens share their powerful stories, sing their hearts out and look sickening while doing it.

episodes.name: Who's Ready for a Dance Off?
episodes.overview: The queens are pushed out of their comfort zones when they are asked not only deliver out of this world vocals but sickening dance breaks that are good enough to impress both the Pop Diva Panel and the drag loving studio audience.

episodes.name: Exposed!
episodes.overview: The queens must bare all and give stripped down performances and a look that incorporates nude illusion. The fate of one contestant hangs in the balance as a medical emergency threatens to derail their placement in the competition.

episodes.name: Battle of the Divas
episodes.overview: The semi-finals find the top four queens paired with one member of the Pop Diva Panel to help guide and mentor them before their next performance. A shocking showdown between two queens shakes up the competition in an unexpected way.

episodes.name: The Winner Is...
episodes.overview: The grand finale has arrived as the top three queens must perform their personal queer anthem as well as a showstopper number. Who will come out on top to be crowned "Queen of the Universe" and win the life-changing cash prize of $250,000?
